1	1	N-Queens	The n-queens puzzle is the problem of placing n queens on an n×n chessboard such that no two queens attack each other. Given an integer n, return all distinct solutions. In each solution, the queens are represented as coordinates in the form of [row, column], where the 0th row and 0th column of the board are indexed from 0. Each solution contains distinct board configurations, and the configurations are returned in any order. Additionally, return the number of distinct solutions.	[{"input": "n = 4", "output": "[[[0,0],[1,2],[2,1],[3,3]], [[0,0],[1,3],[2,1],[3,2]]]", "explanation": "There are two distinct solutions for 4-queens problem."}]	["1 <= n <= 9"]	function nQueens(n):\n    # Return all distinct solutions and the count of solutions\n    pass	Backtracking	Hard	10
2	2	Reverse Linked List	Given the head of a singly linked list, reverse the list and return the new head. The linked list nodes have a value and a pointer to the next node.	[{"input": "head = 1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> 5", "output": "5 -> 4 -> 3 -> 2 -> 1", "explanation": "Reverse the linked list by changing the direction of the pointers."}]	["The number of nodes in the list is in the range [0, 5000]", "-5000 <= Node.val <= 5000"]	function reverseList(head):\n    # Reverse the linked list and return the new head\n    pass	Linked Lists	Easy	3
3	2	Binary Tree Maximum Path Sum	Given the root of a binary tree, return the maximum path sum of any non-empty path. A path is defined as any sequence of nodes from some starting node to any node in the tree along the parent-child connections. The path must contain at least one node and does not need to go through the root.	[{"input": "root = [1,2,3]", "output": 6, "explanation": "The path [2,1,3] has the maximum sum 2 + 1 + 3 = 6."}, {"input": "root = [-10,9,20,null,null,15,7]", "output": 42, "explanation": "The path [15,20,7] has the maximum sum 15 + 20 + 7 = 42."}]	["The number of nodes in the tree is in the range [1, 3 * 10^4]", "-1000 <= Node.val <= 1000"]	function maxPathSum(root):\n    # Return the maximum path sum\n    pass	Trees	Hard	10
4	4	Subarray Sum Equals K	Given an array of integers nums and an integer k, return the total number of continuous subarrays whose sum equals to k.	[{"input": "nums = [1,1,1], k = 2", "output": "2", "explanation": "There are two subarrays that sum to 2: [1,1] and [1,1]"}, {"input": "nums = [-1, -1, 1], k = 0", "output": "1", "explanation": "There is one subarray that sums to 0: [-1, -1, 1]"}]	["1 <= nums.length <= 2 * 10^4", "-1000 <= nums[i] <= 1000", "-10^7 <= k <= 10^7"]	function subarraySum(nums, k):\n    # Return the number of subarrays that sum to k\n    pass	Arrays	Medium	6
